---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import {
  LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE,
  LEGAL_VERSION,
  SITE_NAME,
} from "../../lib/site";

const description = `Privacy Policy for ${SITE_NAME} — draft, pending legal review.`;
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/legal/privacy"
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
      Legal
    </p>
    <h1
      class="font-display mt-3 text-4xl leading-[1.1] font-medium tracking-tight text-[color:var(--color-ink)] sm:text-5xl"
    >
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>

    <dl class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
      <div>
        <dt class="uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs">Version</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">{LEGAL_VERSION}</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs">Effective</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          {LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE}
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs">Status</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Draft — pending legal review
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <aside
      role="note"
      class="mt-8 rounded-lg border border-[color:var(--color-hairline)] bg-[color:var(--color-surface)] p-4 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
    >
      This document is a placeholder. It has not been reviewed by counsel and
      does not yet describe the final data-handling practices of Podex.
      Content will change materially before general availability.
    </aside>

    <div
      class="prose prose-neutral mt-10 max-w-none text-[color:var(--color-ink)] [&_h2]:font-display [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_p]:mt-4 [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_ul]:mt-4 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_li]:mt-1"
    >
      <h2>1. What this policy covers</h2>
      <p>
        This policy describes what information Podex collects when you
        visit the discovery site, and how that information is used. It does not
        yet cover accounts, subscriptions, or billing — those sections will be
        added when those features launch.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Request logs.</strong> Standard server logs (IP address, user
          agent, timestamps, requested paths) may be retained transiently to
          operate the service, diagnose errors, and prevent abuse.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No advertising trackers.</strong> Podex does not embed
          third-party advertising or cross-site tracking scripts.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Fonts.</strong> Typography is loaded from Google Fonts; your
          browser will make requests to `fonts.googleapis.com` and
          `fonts.gstatic.com` when you view the site.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use information</h2>
      <p>
        Information is used only to operate Podex: to serve pages, keep
        the catalog available, investigate incidents, and improve the product.
        It is not sold and it is not shared with advertising networks.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The public discovery site does not set tracking cookies. Strictly
        necessary cookies may be introduced later for account features, and
        will be documented here when they are.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        Podex may link to third-party sites (for example, the original
        podcast feed or the publisher's site). Those sites have their own
        privacy practices and are not covered by this policy.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Operational logs are retained for as short a period as is practical.
        When account features launch, retention windows for user-provided data
        will be documented here.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        Because the public site does not yet identify you, there is no account
        to close and no profile to delete. Requests about this policy can be
        sent to the project maintainers via the project repository.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy as the product evolves. When we do, we will
        bump the version and effective date shown above. Material changes will
        be highlighted for returning users once acceptance capture ships (see
        Terms § 5).
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
